188
00:11:32.275 --> 00:11:33.445
Dear City Council members

189
00:11:33.465 --> 00:11:36.085
and city manager, I sent you a letter earlier this week,

190
00:11:36.085 --> 00:11:39.245
signed by 140 South Portland residents asking the city

191
00:11:39.245 --> 00:11:42.885
to create a short term rent relief program in response

192
00:11:42.885 --> 00:11:44.365
to the financial hardship created

193
00:11:44.425 --> 00:11:47.125
by increased immigration action in our city.

194
00:11:47.625 --> 00:11:49.885
I'm here tonight to make the same request in person.

195
00:11:50.505 --> 00:11:52.885
The council unanimously approved a resolution on

196
00:11:53.165 --> 00:11:55.885
February 3rd that acknowledges that the dramatic disruption

197
00:11:55.885 --> 00:11:58.605
to daily life in South Portland resulting from the surge

198
00:11:58.605 --> 00:12:01.525
caused many residents to miss work or lose business.

199
00:12:01.985 --> 00:12:04.805
The effects of that disruption are ongoing, particularly

200
00:12:04.865 --> 00:12:07.045
for households who have been fractured by Detainments

201
00:12:07.385 --> 00:12:10.285
or who are otherwise struggling to make up the lost income.

202
00:12:11.035 --> 00:12:14.165
Tens of thousands of dollars have already been raised

203
00:12:14.225 --> 00:12:15.845
and distributed within South Portland

204
00:12:16.305 --> 00:12:17.725
to support affected families

205
00:12:17.745 --> 00:12:19.805
and to resolve pending evictions.

206
00:12:20.425 --> 00:12:23.685
But we know there is significant unmet need.

207
00:12:24.355 --> 00:12:28.445
Importantly, we do not know yet what March will look like

208
00:12:28.545 --> 00:12:31.445
as eviction notices cannot be served until March 8th.

209
00:12:31.865 --> 00:12:33.805
We are worried about families that use their savings

210
00:12:33.825 --> 00:12:35.165
and resources available to them

211
00:12:35.185 --> 00:12:36.645
to cover their bills in February.

212
00:12:37.145 --> 00:12:38.605
And now March is due.

213
00:12:39.255 --> 00:12:40.885
There are several funds in Greater Portland

214
00:12:40.945 --> 00:12:42.845
and in the state working to provide rent relief.

215
00:12:43.055 --> 00:12:45.245
Those groups have said publicly that they are struggling

216
00:12:45.245 --> 00:12:47.365
to meet demand creating a variety of sources

217
00:12:47.465 --> 00:12:50.125
for rent relief in this unprecedented moment

218
00:12:51.825 --> 00:12:52.845
and one specifically

219
00:12:52.845 --> 00:12:54.525
to serve South Portland residents is

220
00:12:54.525 --> 00:12:56.405
appropriate and prudent.

221
00:12:56.705 --> 00:12:59.485
Here's what we're asking for the creation of a program

222
00:12:59.625 --> 00:13:02.525
to be funded with money already in the city's undesignated

223
00:13:02.595 --> 00:13:03.845
fund balance and available

224
00:13:03.845 --> 00:13:07.525
for use at the council's discretion to provide rent relief

225
00:13:07.585 --> 00:13:09.365
for any family facing hardship.

226
00:13:09.905 --> 00:13:12.045
The program can be phased and time limited.

227
00:13:12.345 --> 00:13:15.005
For example, it could be funded with $150,000

228
00:13:15.515 --> 00:13:18.845
with the provision that another $150,000 would be provided.

229
00:13:18.905 --> 00:13:20.965
If the first phase of funding is exhausted,

230
00:13:21.305 --> 00:13:23.765
the program could take applications through June 30th.

231
00:13:24.015 --> 00:13:26.045
After those applications are processed,

232
00:13:26.065 --> 00:13:27.605
any remaining money could be returned

233
00:13:27.605 --> 00:13:28.965
to the Undesignated fund.

234
00:13:28.965 --> 00:13:31.965
Balance. Such a program is low risk for the city,

235
00:13:32.265 --> 00:13:33.845
making money already in hand

236
00:13:33.845 --> 00:13:35.285
available to people who need it.

237
00:13:35.585 --> 00:13:37.685
It would protect landlords from lost income

238
00:13:37.705 --> 00:13:39.605
and residents from becoming unhoused.

239
00:13:39.825 --> 00:13:41.445
If the money is not needed, it returns

240
00:13:41.445 --> 00:13:43.205
to the undesignated fund balance.

241
00:13:44.005 --> 00:13:46.645
I have two questions I would like answered if possible.

242
00:13:47.235 --> 00:13:50.045
It's my understanding that the existing GA program requires

243
00:13:50.045 --> 00:13:51.925
applicants to prove their financial hardship

244
00:13:51.925 --> 00:13:53.125
and their inability to work.

245
00:13:53.655 --> 00:13:55.325
Would it be feasible for the city

246
00:13:55.345 --> 00:13:58.685
to create a parallel temporary program using the same

247
00:13:59.005 --> 00:14:02.205
hardship eligibility parameters without the requirement

248
00:14:02.205 --> 00:14:03.365
regarding work status?

249
00:14:03.465 --> 00:14:06.445
30 seconds. What additional resources, if any,

250
00:14:06.445 --> 00:14:08.005
would the city staff need in order

251
00:14:08.025 --> 00:14:09.685
to create such a short term program?

252
00:14:10.535 --> 00:14:13.285
Thank you for your consideration of this important issue.

253
00:14:15.335 --> 00:14:18.125
Thank you very much. Thank you to Chelsea,

254
00:14:18.465 --> 00:14:20.085
who you said you represented.

255
00:14:23.555 --> 00:14:25.845
Good evening. My name is Emily Hanson.

256
00:14:25.915 --> 00:14:28.805
This is my daughter Margo. We live on Hillside Avenue.

257
00:14:29.575 --> 00:14:31.565
We're here tonight to strongly urge you

258
00:14:31.585 --> 00:14:34.245
to consider the proposed rent relief program.

259
00:14:35.295 --> 00:14:36.485
Since mid-January,

260
00:14:36.785 --> 00:14:38.805
we have been helping a family in South Portland

261
00:14:39.305 --> 00:14:41.205
who are unable to leave their home due

262
00:14:41.205 --> 00:14:42.285
to fear of deportation.

263
00:14:42.825 --> 00:14:45.685
It has been eye-opening to see what this family has been

