00:14:45.685 --> 00:14:46.965
through over the past few months,

265
00:14:47.465 --> 00:14:49.525
and they have written a statement for me to share

266
00:14:49.525 --> 00:14:51.485
with you all tonight about their experience.

267
00:14:52.785 --> 00:14:55.205
The recent ice operations are terrifying.

268
00:14:55.805 --> 00:14:58.085
A friend was arrested while driving home from dropping

269
00:14:58.105 --> 00:14:59.285
his child off at school.

270
00:15:00.355 --> 00:15:03.325
He's a dedicated, vetted worker with no criminal record

271
00:15:03.625 --> 00:15:05.765
and a, an act of asylum application,

272
00:15:06.025 --> 00:15:07.325
but he was taken anyway.

273
00:15:08.465 --> 00:15:10.605
His children are without a head of household

274
00:15:10.665 --> 00:15:13.285
and other immigrant families are afraid to send their kids

275
00:15:13.305 --> 00:15:17.085
to school, including me bringing a sense of panic

276
00:15:17.185 --> 00:15:19.165
and fear for my family and the community.

277
00:15:20.105 --> 00:15:21.765
My wife has a five month old baby

278
00:15:22.145 --> 00:15:24.645
and I'm the only one that can work and help my family out.

279
00:15:24.825 --> 00:15:28.245
But I couldn't. My landlord sent us an eviction letter

280
00:15:28.245 --> 00:15:29.725
because I couldn't pay my rent.

281
00:15:30.525 --> 00:15:33.565
I stayed stressed with my family not sleeping at night.

282
00:15:34.935 --> 00:15:36.805
While working with this family, I saw

283
00:15:36.825 --> 00:15:38.845
how quickly things can unravel once the

284
00:15:38.845 --> 00:15:40.085
eviction processes started.

285
00:15:41.215 --> 00:15:44.405
There are legal costs, more time off work for meetings,

286
00:15:44.425 --> 00:15:46.965
transportation to organize, et cetera.

287
00:15:47.655 --> 00:15:49.005
Thankfully, for this family

288
00:15:49.025 --> 00:15:51.805
and many others, we were able to help them get back on track

289
00:15:51.805 --> 00:15:53.965
with their rent before they were evicted.

290
00:15:54.345 --> 00:15:56.285
But there may be others who have fallen behind

291
00:15:56.625 --> 00:15:58.885
and are at risk for eviction in March.

292
00:16:00.505 --> 00:16:03.845
The moral imperative to help help these families is clear.

293
00:16:04.345 --> 00:16:06.445
And this proposal would be economical,

294
00:16:07.085 --> 00:16:09.285
economically beneficial for South Portland as well.

295
00:16:10.185 --> 00:16:12.685
Modest financial support for those who are

296
00:16:12.685 --> 00:16:14.645
behind in their rent will prevent

297
00:16:14.655 --> 00:16:16.485
downstream municipal costs.

298
00:16:17.275 --> 00:16:21.485
When a family becomes displaced, CLO costs don't disappear.

299
00:16:21.715 --> 00:16:24.325
They shift to the city with loss of revenue

300
00:16:24.945 --> 00:16:27.325
and workforce emergency shelter

301
00:16:27.425 --> 00:16:30.005
or mo motel placements costing between three

302
00:16:30.185 --> 00:16:32.405
and $5,000 per month per family.

303
00:16:33.095 --> 00:16:34.765
There are increased utilization

304
00:16:34.765 --> 00:16:37.685
of general assistance school system disruptions,

305
00:16:37.685 --> 00:16:40.445
healthcare strain, higher public safety

306
00:16:40.625 --> 00:16:43.485
and emergency response use and legal

307
00:16:43.665 --> 00:16:45.005
and administrative costs.

308
00:16:46.275 --> 00:16:49.405
This all results in much more work for the city staff.

309
00:16:50.465 --> 00:16:52.565
In summary, preventing eviction

310
00:16:52.585 --> 00:16:56.285
and displacement costs the city much less than responding

311
00:16:56.285 --> 00:16:57.925
to it, and it's the right thing to do.

